. For the Bianchi V and VII classes the\nradial spinor breaks all of supersymmetry. We briefly discuss the conditions\nfor possible massive supersymmetric Bianchi solutions by generalizing the\nmatter content to include tensor, hypermultiplets and a generic gauging on the\nR symmetry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Oct 2016 19:14:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Oct 2016 17:20:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 23 Jan 2017 13:34:24 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 21 May 2017 17:47:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-27"}
